# 7. 願い

Kanade: ...
Kanade: (I can't go back and change what happened that day...)
Kanade: (There's no use in wanting to...)
Kanade: I have to keep composing. That's all I can do now...
Ena: <Huh? K? You're still working?>
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: <Did you already take that bath?>
Ena: <Yeah, I feel pretty refreshed now. I might actually be able to finish one of my illustrations.>
Kanade: <Okay. I'll be working like normal, so let me know if anything comes up.>
Ena: <Okay, I will.>
Ena: <Hey, K, I wanna ask you something...>
Ena: <My illustration for the post-chorus feels kinda dark at the moment, but I'm wondering if I should add a little more light... What do you think?>
Kanade: <Well... ...>
Ena: <K...?>
Kanade: <Oh, sorry... I was thinking about something else, so I couldn't gather my thoughts properly.>
Ena: <Oh, are you talking about your future...?>
Kanade: <It's not bothering me that much, but it does keep nagging at me.>
Ena: <Right...>
Kanade: <But I'm okay... I feel a lot better after talking with Rin just now.>
Ena: <Wait, with Rin?>
Kanade: <Yes...>
Kanade: <I tried thinking about what I want to do, but I couldn't come up with anything...>
Kanade: <However, there was a time when I really loved music more than anything else...>
Ena: <Really...?>
Ena: <Can you tell me why...?>
Kanade: <Sure. My happiest memories all seem to involve music in some way...>
Kanade: <My mom and dad always smiled whenever they heard a song that I composed.>
Kanade: <I really loved those moments...>
Ena: <I see...>
Ena: <That explains why your songs feel so warm, K.>
Kanade: <What...?>
Ena: <The memories you just mentioned might be the source of the warmth I feel in your songs. It makes so much sense now.>
Ena: <So, are you gonna keep composing after you graduate?>
Kanade: <Oh, um... Yes. I plan to keep on composing.>
Kanade: <Especially... Since that's what I need to do...>
Ena: <What...?>
Ena: <Wait, what do you mean...?>
Kanade: <...>
Kanade: <I realized something while talking about this...>
Kanade: <No matter how many songs I do compose, I'll never be able to feel the warmth I did back then ever again...>
Ena: <Oh...>
Kanade: <I know there's nothing I can do about that now...>
Kanade: <But my dad losing his ability to compose is still my fault...>
Kanade: <That's why I need to keep composing. For him. For everyone.>
Ena: <S-Stop right there for a second!>
Kanade: <Huh...?>
Ena: <What about...>
Ena: <What about your happiness, K?>
Kanade: <My happiness...?>
Kanade: <If I can compose songs that save others, then I'll...>
Ena: <Kanade, listen.>
Kanade: <Huh...?>
Ena: <I know you feel awful about what happened to your dad, but there's no point in beating yourself up...>
Ena: <What I'm trying to say is... I think your happiness is a separate issue.>
Ena: <Personally, I don't want those two things being so closely tied together...!>
Ena: <I mean, you're working so hard for the sake of others...! You deserve to be happy too!>
Kanade: <Oh...>
Kanade's Mother: Wanting to learn how to write wonderful songs like your father is a beautiful dream.
Kanade's Mother: But I'll be happy as long as you find something that makes you happy, Kanade.
Kanade: <But...>
???: <I agree with what she's saying.>
Ena: <Huh?>
Kanade: <KAITO...?>
KAITO: <You tried to suppress whatever you were feeling just now...>
Kanade: <What I was feeling...?>
KAITO: <Yes...>
KAITO: <You believe that you're not allowed to be happy. That you have no right to.>
KAITO: <Am I wrong...?>
Kanade: <I...>
KAITO: <What are you always telling Mafuyu...?>
KAITO: <To cherish her feelings.>
KAITO: <I'm okay with you composing songs in order to save others and make them feel happy.>
KAITO: <But I'm not okay with you turning a blind eye to what you're really feeling...>
Kanade: <What I'm really feeling...?>
Kanade: <B-But...>
Ena: <Actually, Kanade...>
Kanade: <Huh...?>
Ena: <Before you formed N25, and even now... The songs you've composed have helped me so much.>
Ena: <Every time I listen to one of your songs whenever I'm not feeling great... Whenever I wonder if I should continue drawing, the thought of creating art for N25 keeps me going.>
Kanade: <Ena...>
Ena: <Yeah, I feel pain sometimes when I'm working on an illustration... But I want to keep drawing.>
Ena: <Plus, I've actually started thinking about what I wanna do after I graduate.>
Ena: <I doubt I'd be giving that any serious thought if I hadn't joined N25...>
Kanade: <...>
Ena: <I mean, Kanade.>
Ena: <You're the reason why I'm even thinking about my own future.>
Ena: <It's a small step, but I have something to work towards now...>
Ena: <So, Kanade... I think you should also do what makes you the happiest.>
KAITO: <If there is something you wish to do, you shouldn't fight against it.>
KAITO: <Because there's no way you'll be able to save her if you don't cherish your own feelings.>
Kanade: <Oh...>
Ena: <KAITO, wait! Ugh. He always storms off after saying whatever it is that's on his mind...>
Kanade: <...>
Kanade: (Is it really okay for me to do that...?)
Kanade: (Am I allowed to feel the way I did back then...?)
Kanade: (But I robbed Dad of his future...)
Kanade: (Still...)
Kanade: (If....it's okay...)
Kanade: If it's actually okay, then...
